  "text": "In this section, we evaluate the performance of the proposed 3 × 3 distributed space-time code used by the relays in synchronous as well as asynchronous transmission compared to its corresponding perfect code. The performance of the 2 × 2 scheme has already been presented in [CITATION_1] . Recalling the cooperative system model of Section II, a virtual MIMO scheme is assumed with = 3 transmit antennas and = 3 receive antennas. The decoding is performed using the Sphere Decoder. However in the case of asynchronous relays, the codewords are transmitted over + max symbol intervals resulting in rank deficiency of the channel matrix. In order to tackle this problem, the MMSE-DFE preprocessing is required to precede the lattice decoding so that the transformed channel has always full rank.",
